attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai families. It exhibits classic botnet behavior including: 1) Environment discovery and anti-analysis via extensive /proc filesystem enumeration (/proc/cpuinfo, /proc/maps, /proc/cmdline) to identify and kill competing bot processes using syscall 62 (sys_kill). 2) Network communication for GeoIP discovery using hardcoded HTTP requests ('GET /geoip/?res=20&r') to identify its external location. 3) Multiple dedicated DDoS attack modules (sub_401e18, sub_402c66, sub_403469) that use raw sockets to craft and flood UDP, TCP, and game-specific (SAMP) packets. 4) Self-backgrounding and persistence techniques using fork and setsid. 5) Custom encryption/obfuscation (sub_404372) to hide its configuration and Command & Control (C2) communication protocol.
